attributes.Long form description: The student worked with a nintendo switch, starting by disassembling the joy with controllers and then assembling them in the comfort grip, continuing with disassembling it, leaving the controls on the table, then assembling the controls in the straps, then disassembling them and assembling them in the nintendo switch, pulling the kickstand and changing the game card, then changing the SD card, then turning on the nintendo switch and ending the video by turning it off.

attributes.Transcription: Now please change the controller from the handheld mode it is currently in into the Joy-Con comfort grip.

attributes.Action sentence: The student disassembles the Joy-Con controllers from the Nintendo switch.

attributes.Action Correctness: Wrong Action, corrected by instructor verbally
attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: You need to put the blue on the left and the red on the right side

attributes.Action sentence: The student assembles the Joy-Con controllers into the comfort grip.

attributes.Transcription: You need to put the blue on the left and the red on the right side

attributes.Action Correctness: Wrong Action, corrected by instructor verbally

attributes.Transcription: The other way around, so the bumper show when you have the controller in your hand.

attributes.Action Correctness: Wrong Action, corrected by instructor verbally
attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The comfort_grip should be the other way around.

attributes.Transcription: Well done
Now please change the controller from the comfort grip to the two individual joycons.

attributes.Action sentence: The student disassembles the Joy-Con controllers from the comfort grip
The student lift the Nintendo Switch tablet from the table

attributes.Transcription: The two Joy-Con holders are on the right side

attributes.Action sentence: The student assembles the Joy-Con straps to the Joy-Con controllers

attributes.Transcription: Attach them to the Joy-Cons.
Make sure to line up plus and plus, and minus to minus.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: Make sure to line up plus and plus, and minus to minus.

attributes.Transcription: And press the white button, the white thing at the bottom.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: And press the white button, the white thing at the bottom.
And press the white button, the white thing at the bottom.

attributes.Transcription: Well done
Now please change the controllers from the Joy-Cons back to the switch itself.

attributes.Action sentence: The student disassembles the right Joy-Con strap.
The student assembles the right Joy-Con controller into the Nintendo switch
The student disassembles the left Joy-Con strap.
The student assembles the left Joy-Con controller into the Nintendo switch.

attributes.Transcription: Nice, well done
Now please stand the Nintendo on the table using the kickstand, the kickstand's at the back of the Nintendo switch, you just need to pull out.

attributes.Action sentence: The student pulls out the kickstand.

attributes.Transcription: Nice, well done.
Now please change the game card of the Nintendo switch.

attributes.Action sentence: The student exchanges the game cards.

attributes.Transcription: well done, Now please change the micro SD card of the Nintendo switch.

attributes.Action sentence: The student exchanges the micro SD card.

attributes.Transcription: The SD card is located behind the kickstand.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The SD card is located behind the kickstand.

attributes.Transcription: Push it in all, just in case
well done,Now please turn on the Nintendo switch.

attributes.Action sentence: The student turns on the Nintendo switch

attributes.Transcription: well done, now please turn off the Nintendo switch, you will have to hold the buttom for three seconds, go to power options and turn it off.

attributes.Action sentence: The student turns off the Nintendo switch

attributes.Transcription: Well done.
You can stop the recording now.
